    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1029"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1029">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312:52/254a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                        General <persName type="to">Hanna</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 27, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department regrets profoundly your arrest by the Federal authorities and the
                    indignities to which you were subjected at their hands; and rejoices that you
                    escaped without physical injury. It sympathizes with you in the humiliation
                    which you feel at the outrage suffered by you as the representative of your
                    Government; question of redress will have due consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
